        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tool-Use Benchmarks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tool-use benchmarks evaluate how accurately an agent selects the right API, constructs valid arguments, and chains multiple calls to complete a goal. They differ from general agent benchmarks like GAIA or WebArena in that the task environment is a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function-calling interface",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " rather than a browser or operating system — success is measured by whether the correct tool was called with the correct parameters, not by the downstream effect in a live system."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benchmark Landscape"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Tool-use benchmark landscape: ToolBench, BFCL, and API-Bank"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Three benchmarks cover most of the tool-use evaluation space: ToolBench (large-scale API chaining), BFCL (fine-grained function-calling accuracy), and API-Bank (tiered difficulty with retrieval). They complement each other — a model can score well on BFCL's simple single-call cases yet fail ToolBench's multi-step API chains."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ToolBench"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ToolBench tests multi-step tool use across 16,464 real-world APIs drawn from RapidAPI. Each task requires calling multiple APIs in sequence, using the output of one call as input to the next. The evaluator checks both "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "pass rate",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (whether the task is completed correctly) and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "win rate",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (whether the model's answer is preferred over a GPT-3.5 baseline by an LLM judge)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Loading ToolBench Tasks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# pip install datasets\nfrom datasets import load_dataset\n\ntoolbench = load_dataset(\"ToolBench/ToolBench\", split=\"test\")\n\ntask = toolbench[0]\nprint(task[\"conversations\"][0][\"value\"])  # user instruction\nprint(task[\"tools\"])                      # available tool schemas (OpenAI format)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Running an Agent on ToolBench"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\nimport json\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\ndef toolbench_to_anthropic(tools: list[dict]) -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"Convert ToolBench tool schema (OpenAI format) to Anthropic format.\"\"\"\n    result = []\n    for t in tools:\n        fn = t.get(\"function\", t)   # handle both wrapped and flat formats\n        result.append({\n            \"name\": fn[\"name\"],\n            \"description\": fn.get(\"description\", \"\"),\n            \"input_schema\": fn.get(\"parameters\", {\"type\": \"object\", \"properties\": {}}),\n        })\n    return result\n\n\ndef run_toolbench_task(task: dict, model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\", max_steps=10):\n    messages = []\n    # Build the conversation up to the last user turn\n    for turn in task[\"conversations\"]:\n        if turn[\"from\"] == \"human\":\n            messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": turn[\"value\"]})\n            break   # run from the first user instruction\n\n    tools = toolbench_to_anthropic(task[\"tools\"])\n\n    for step in range(max_steps):\n        resp = client.messages.create(\n            model=model,\n            max_tokens=2048,\n            tools=tools,\n            messages=messages,\n        )\n        messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": resp.content})\n\n        tool_results = []\n        for block in resp.content:\n            if block.type == \"tool_use\":\n                # In evaluation, the harness provides real API responses.\n                # Here we simulate with a placeholder.\n                tool_results.append({\n                    \"type\": \"tool_result\",\n                    \"tool_use_id\": block.id,\n                    \"content\": json.dumps({\"status\": \"ok\", \"data\": \"simulated response\"}),\n                })\n\n        if not tool_results:\n            break   # model stopped using tools\n\n        messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": tool_results})\n\n    # Extract final text response\n    final = next(\n        (b.text for b in resp.content if b.type == \"text\"), \"\"\n    )\n    return final, messages\n"
          }
        ]
      },
