            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tool-use benchmarks isolate the function-calling layer from the broader agentic loop. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "BFCL",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the most granular for measuring call accuracy across seven categories and maintains a live leaderboard. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ToolBench",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " scales to real-world API diversity and multi-step planning. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "API-Bank",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " adds the retrieval dimension that operational agents face. Combining results across all three gives the clearest picture of where a model's tool-use breaks down: selection, argument formation, sequencing, or abstaining when no tool fits."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
